Package: drma
Title: Dose-Response Meta-Analysis with a meta/netmeta-Style Interface
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Yuuki", "Furukawa", email = "ykfrkw@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0376-4119"))
Description: A meta/netmeta-style wrapper around the 'dosresmeta' package
    (Crippa & Orsini 2016 <doi:10.1186/s12874-016-0189-0>) for one-stage
    dose-response meta-analysis (Crippa et al. 2019
    <doi:10.1177/0962280218773122>). Accepts arm-level data in long format
    and automatically computes OR, RR, MD, or SMD before fitting restricted
    cubic spline dose-response curves (or linear, log-linear, and quadratic
    alternatives). Provides plot methods with bubble overlays and rug marks,
    multi-curve overlay for sensitivity analyses, predictions at arbitrary
    doses with optional absolute-risk conversion, target-dose estimation
    (ED50/ED95), and a pairwise league table.
